m><title><![CDATA["Charlie’s bloody coat was returned to Erika": Candace Owens releases unseen SUV photos after Charlie Kirk's assassination, raises new questions]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132026830.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Candace Owens has released previously unseen photos from the SUV that transported Charlie Kirk to the hospital after he was fatally shot, claiming they raise new questions about the events following the attack. She pointed to shattered glass, a blood-stained bag, and Kirk's damaged microphone, while questioning how evidence was handled. Owens also highlighted alleged inconsistencies in witness accounts. However, her claims remain her interpretation and have not been officially verified by investigators.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/charlies-bloody-coat-was-returned-to-erika-candace-owens-releases-unseen-suv-photos-after-charlie-kirks-assassination-raises-new-questions/articleshow/132026830.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/charlies-bloody-coat-was-returned-to-erika-candace-owens-releases-unseen-suv-photos-after-charlie-kirks-assassination-raises-new-questions/articleshow/132026830.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T05:31:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132026830,imgsize-115490.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Planning a trip to India? Here's why flight tickets from UAE are getting cheaper ]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132036291.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-india-airfares-drop-ahead-of-july-travel-rush-kerala-routes-see-sharpest-dip-report/articleshow/132036291.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-india-airfares-drop-ahead-of-july-travel-rush-kerala-routes-see-sharpest-dip-report/articleshow/132036291.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T19:41:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132036679,imgsize-180530.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[D4vd murder case takes new turn as prosecutors reveal alleged motive before July court hearing and not guilty plea]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132022967.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The criminal case involving singer D4vd remains active in California. Prosecutors allege he killed 14-year-old Celeste Rivas Hernandez to stop her from exposing an alleged relationship, while the defense strongly denies those claims. Burke has pleaded not guilty, and the court will continue hearing the case, with a preliminary hearing scheduled for July 21, 2026.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/d4vd-murder-case-takes-new-turn-as-prosecutors-reveal-alleged-motive-before-july-court-hearing-and-not-guilty-plea/articleshow/132022967.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/d4vd-murder-case-takes-new-turn-as-prosecutors-reveal-alleged-motive-before-july-court-hearing-and-not-guilty-plea/articleshow/132022967.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T23:43:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132022937,imgsize-73519.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hundreds of flights delayed at Heathrow and Gatwick as thunderstorms hit Southern England]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132034750.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Severe thunderstorms unleashed travel chaos across southern England, grounding hundreds of flights at Heathrow and Gatwick.  Torrential rain, lightning, and hail forced air traffic control to implement safety restrictions, leading to significant delays and passengers facing long waits.  While storms are expected to move on, airlines warn that flight schedules may take time to fully recover, impacting travellers throughout the day.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/hundreds-of-flights-delayed-at-heathrow-and-gatwick-as-thunderstorms-hit-southern-england/articleshow/132034750.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/hundreds-of-flights-delayed-at-heathrow-and-gatwick-as-thunderstorms-hit-southern-england/articleshow/132034750.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T17:52:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132034772,imgsize-550649.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Flying from UAE to India? Here's what you need to know as India brings back Air Suvidha portal]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132034604.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/flying-from-uae-to-india-heres-why-you-need-to-fill-air-suvidha-2-0-health-form-before-boarding/articleshow/132034604.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/flying-from-uae-to-india-heres-why-you-need-to-fill-air-suvidha-2-0-health-form-before-boarding/articleshow/132034604.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T17:49:48+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132034755,imgsize-96516.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[President Sheikh Mohamed orders Dh10 million relief package for Venezuela quake victims]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132033818.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Venezuela is reeling from devastating earthquakes, with rescue teams desperately searching for survivors. In a swift response, the United Arab Emirates has pledged Dh10 million in emergency humanitarian aid, directed by President His Highness Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan. This significant contribution underscores the UAE's unwavering commitment to global humanitarian assistance during times of crisis, offering crucial support to the disaster-stricken nation.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/president-sheikh-mohamed-orders-dh10-million-relief-package-for-venezuela-quake-victims/articleshow/132033818.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/president-sheikh-mohamed-orders-dh10-million-relief-package-for-venezuela-quake-victims/articleshow/132033818.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T17:12:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132033896,imgsize-79112.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UAE expands visa-on-arrival to 6 more countries, offering eligible travellers up to 60-day stay]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132033482.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Indian and Filipino passport holders can now enjoy easier entry into the UAE with an expanded visa-on-arrival program.  Previously requiring visas from select Western nations, eligible travelers now benefit from this facility if they hold valid visas or residency from Australia, Canada, Japan, New Zealand, Singapore, or South Korea. This initiative aims to boost tourism and business ties, offering 14-day or 60-day stay options.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-expands-visa-on-arrival-to-6-more-countries-offering-eligible-travellers-up-to-60-day-stay/articleshow/132033482.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/uae-expands-visa-on-arrival-to-6-more-countries-offering-eligible-travellers-up-to-60-day-stay/articleshow/132033482.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T16:46:02+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132033531,imgsize-105756.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['22 killed, 576 arrested': Pakistan accused of brutal crackdown in PoJK at UNHRC]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132031901.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/22-killed-576-arrested-pakistan-accused-of-brutal-crackdown-in-pok-at-unhrc/articleshow/132031901.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/22-killed-576-arrested-pakistan-accused-of-brutal-crackdown-in-pok-at-unhrc/articleshow/132031901.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-27T15:14:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132032337,imgsize-1195884.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Xi's military purge widens: China strips 6 generals, ex-Politburo member of lawmaker posts]]></title><d